Adjusting the co-ordinates of X and Y - axis, the quadrants. 9

When Adjusting the co-ordinates, normally to make it dynamic, you put a calculation here. but for now, I used manual set up.


Note: The Final PBIX with the co-ordinates adjusted has been uploaded for your convenience. Download from the above button.

Steps :

  1. Click the scatter plot chart.
  2. Click the "Analytics" tab from Visualization pane.
  3. Open the drill down of the x-axis Constant Line 1
  4. Click Add
  5. Set Value: 0.5
  6. Color: Black 40%
  7. Line Style: Solid

Steps :

  1. Click the scatter plot chart.
  2. Click the "Analytics" tab from Visualization pane.
  3. Open the drill down of the Y-axis Constant Line 1
  4. Click Add
  5. Set Value: 20
  6. Color: Black 40%
  7. Line Style: Solid

  1. Steps :
    1. Click the scatter plot chart.
    2. Click the "Format" tab from Visualization pane.
    3. Open the drill down of the x-axis 
    4. Set Start: (-0.5)
    5. Set End: 2

  1. Steps :
    1. Click the scatter plot chart.
    2. Click the "Format" tab from Visualization pane.
    3. Open the drill down of the Y-axis 
    4. Set Start: (-20)
    5. Set End: 50

  1. Steps :
    1. Click the scatter plot chart.
    2. Click the "Format" tab from Visualization pane.
    3. Set Catagory Label: ON
